texts.text: >The demons form ranks as they advance on the Liberators.
>Chi You approaches them and block their path...
*Roar*
*Shriek*
A-All those demons just like that...
He's so strong! It'd be even better if we had one more on our side!
How can someone become so strong...?
Through battles. Fight, be victorious, rinse and repeat, and grow stronger.
You would never be able to attain such power in this state of peace, humans.
Anyway, we've gotten pretty far already. How does a quick break sound?
Yo, there ain't anywhere here for us to do that...
I'm looking for a good enough spot away from all those demons.
But it might end up costing too much energy.
Resting when you can is a fundamental battlefield tactic.
And we still don't know where all the people that got kidnapped went.
If we spend all our energy on that, we'll be in real trouble.

Shionyan's right!
She never misses a thing!
Aight, let's take a quick breather...
And while you guys do, I'll go for a quick scout.
Yo, what happened to restin' when you can?
I'm used to this, You guys aren't. I've got plenty left in the tank.
That's why I should be gathering as much intel as I can.
But isn't it dangerous to go out there alone?
I shall accompany you. I have the most battlefield experience out of anybody here.
I shall even fight off any scouts that we may encounter.
These two gonna be okay being left alone like this?
He might have a hidden army somewhere that's ready to go at his command.
I would never use such deceitful tactics.
And I am certainly not aiding the demons who have been attacking you.
Thanks, I guess.
We'll be fine. I can always find my way back by retracing my footsteps.
Anyway, see you guys later.
So what made you want to tag along? You here to ask me something...?
Ah, you saw through my ruse. Indeed, there is something that I wish to ask of you.
Why do you not wish to fight?

Hey, we are fighting.
Against all those demons...
No, you are all capable of much more than what you have been showing me.
You Liberators are quite an impressive bunch.
You must have overcome much to get here. I can tell that you are formidable warriors.
But being a foot soldier and a commander are very different things.
Your strategy and tactics leave much to be desired.
That is what the Liberators lack. In that regard, out of your entire group,
you and that Vince character are the only ones making any real contributions.
Vince in particular...
His eyes have seen war. He must have experienced it recently.
What say you?
I can tell that you have also seen war. You were formerly a soldier, were you not?
But your eyes have become used to peace and your mind has begun to rot.
You have relinquished command over to someone less experience in war,
and are easily swayed by a wench. Very unbecoming of a true warrior.
In reality, you should be the one commanding this group.
You should be the one leading the Liberators, no?
So I ask again. Why do you not wish to fight?
Why are you not training your body and striving to attain a position of power?
Hey, I'm not exactly a perfect human or anything...
Yeah, I used to be a mercenary, but that was just an extension of my hobby.
I never wanted to lead or grow stronger.
I didn't become a mercenary because I had noble goals in mind.
I got tired of the battlefield.
If I wanted to become a commander or something,
I'd still be a soldier.
Tired of the battlefield...? Not war?
I have nothing against war or conflict. I have a problem with why it happens.
There was no point in me being out there.
But fighting as a Liberator is a good enough reason for me.
It's why I'm fighting against these demons.
*Nod*
Anyway, enough talk. Let's get back to work.
Understood.
We found one of their base camps while out scouting.
Aight, let's roll out!

Enemies incoming!
The humans are attacking!
Humans?! Where?!
Yo, right here!
Humans? What is the meaning of this...?
B-Brother?!
Well met, brother.
What are you doing here?
Did you finally decide to participate in our little contest?!
Which means these humans must be at your command...
No, I am simply aiding the Liberators.
You helping someone else? Humans of all things as well!
They too must have felt the pain that peace brought them!
Let us start our great war and destroy their precious world!
No, we are here to stop that from happening.
What...?
Yo, buddy, mind stoppin' all this senseless fightin'?
I mean, what are you plannin' to accomplish by bringin' war to our world?
There's a million other ways to "fight", you know?
T-This is who you are aiding...?
Yes.
N-No, how can this be?! What happened to you, brother?!
Who would admit defeat before the battle has taken place?! It is pure nonsense!
What has gotten into you, brother...? I-It must be these humans' doing!
They have become slothful and ignorant because of their precious peace!
You are to be dealt with at once!
Someone's not willing to listen to reason.

Aight, let's do this!
Devil Download!

*Wince*
How can mere humans...?
We won, but we ended up fighting after all that...
We had no choice. They were itching to fight from the start.
There's no way of getting through to someone in that state.
Not only that, it's our duty to fight against demons like that.
To protect people, you know?
Yeah...
(They fight to protect their brethren.)
(What reward is there in choosing such a path...?)
